<item>
  <title>Patina Portrait</title>
  <dc:creator>Rudy </dc:creator>
  <link>https://thomascwells.com/sandstonesonnets/poems/patina-portrait.html</link>
  <description><![CDATA[ 




<p>Look across the canyon face,<br>
A weathered man holds his place.<br>
With hair of brown and moustache too,<br>
A coat of varnish, earthen hue.</p>
<p>No brush has touched this rocky wall,<br>
Yet nature’s paint outshines them all.<br>
An Old West portrait formed in desert glaze,<br>
Was he a sheriff? Merchant? Who’s to say?</p>
<p>His eyes are gone, worn smooth by time,<br>
Yet still he keeps a watch sublime.<br>
Flume canyon rests beneath his gaze,<br>
An old prospector from those bygone days?</p>
<p>So give a nod as you pass on by,<br>
This stoic stranger won’t reply.<br>
But desert varnish keeps him near,<br>
A patinaed figure from yesteryear.</p>
