<item>
  <title>The Canyon’s Secret Grin</title>
  <dc:creator>Rudy </dc:creator>
  <link>https://thomascwells.com/sandstonesonnets/poems/canyon-secret-grin.html</link>
  <description><![CDATA[ 




<p>If you search the canyon wall,<br>
A cheeky smile grins down at all.<br>
Red rock carved by wind and time,<br>
Sharing nature’s favorite rhyme.</p>
<p>Green trees giggle from above,<br>
Junipers whisper tales of love.<br>
While hikers stop and point with glee:<br>
“Look! The canyon’s smiling at me!”</p>
<p>This sandstone jester never frowns,<br>
Just grins at all the desert towns.<br>
A million-year-old happy face,<br>
That makes D4 such a lovely place!</p>
<p>So if you’re walking Fruita’s trails<br>
And need a laugh when courage fails,<br>
Just look up at that crimson wall,<br>
The canyon’s smiling after all!</p>
