<item>
  <title>The Dapper Duck of Fruita</title>
  <dc:creator>Rudy </dc:creator>
  <link>https://thomascwells.com/sandstonesonnets/poems/dapper-duck.html</link>
  <description><![CDATA[ 




<p>Near Fruita stands a rock so odd,<br>
A sandstone duck that gives a nod.<br>
With fancy hat perched on its head,<br>
It looks like royalty instead!</p>
<p>This stony fowl with fashion sense<br>
Makes tourists stop in pure suspense.<br>
“Is that a duck wearing a hat?”<br>
“Or am I stoned?” (It might be that!)</p>
<p>The Colorado winds may blow,<br>
But duckie’s hat won’t ever go.<br>
While other ducks must swim and fly,<br>
This one just winks at passers-by.</p>
