<item>
  <title>Red Rock Fury</title>
  <dc:creator>Rudy </dc:creator>
  <link>https://thomascwells.com/sandstonesonnets/poems/red-rock-fury.html</link>
  <description><![CDATA[ 




<p>Perched in the desert, proud and absurd,<br>
A sandstone cliff — an Angry Bird.<br>
Its beak juts sharp, its brow is stern,<br>
As if it’s awaiting its turn to burn.</p>
<p>The wind plays slingshot, the clouds take aim,<br>
But this rock just chuckles, immune to the game.<br>
Forever frozen in feathery guise,<br>
A grumpy guardian under bluebird skies.</p>
<p>Lizards parade by its scowling face,<br>
Whispering tales of this lofty place.<br>
Tourists snap photos, delighted to find,<br>
A relic of pixels in stone redefined.</p>
<p>And when twilight paints the canyon red,<br>
The Angry Bird will live on in your head.<br>
A game once played on a glowing screen,<br>
Now etched by time in a desert scene.</p>
